Everton star, Alex Iwobi, was among the first set of players to arrive in Singapore ahead of Nigeria’s next international match against Brazil. The Super Eagles will take on the Selecao on Sunday afternoon at the Singapore National Stadium. According to Soccernet, Iwobi arrived alongside Leicester City’s Wilfred Ndidi and Udinese star, William Troost Ekong. The newspaper reports that Super Eagles head coach, Gernot Rohr was also part of the group which include Chidozie Awaziem (FC Porto), Ramon Azeez (Granada), Victor Osimhen (Lille) and Maduka Okoye (Fortuna Düsseldorf II), Samuel Chukwueze (Villarreal), Emmanuel Dennis (Club Brugge). Rohr’s men head to the game following a 2-2 draw with Ukraine in their last friendly game. Nigeria were defeated 3-0 by Brazil in an international friendly encounter at the Abuja National Stadium in 2003. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.